WEBVTT

00:05.072 --> 00:07.939
- To all my friends,

00:07.942 --> 00:10.676
peers and fellow students.

00:10.678 --> 00:15.681
I'm so honoured to
accept this crown

00:15.683 --> 00:18.117
as your prom queen.

00:21.422 --> 00:24.423
And I wish you all the
greatest success.

00:24.425 --> 00:28.560
Because if you really
want it, you can have it!

00:31.032 --> 00:33.132
Ugh!

00:35.000 --> 00:41.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:31.759 --> 01:33.892
<i>- Hi! You've reached
Joanne Harvey.</i>

01:33.894 --> 01:35.394
<i>Please leave me a message.</i>

01:35.396 --> 01:36.929
-<i> Joanne!</i>

01:36.931 --> 01:38.330
I just got your card,

01:38.332 --> 01:40.666
and you are a star
for remembering.

01:40.668 --> 01:43.802
Thank you so much. Call me.
Let's have dinner.

02:05.960 --> 02:07.793
- What do you think?

02:07.795 --> 02:09.428
- Very scholarly.

02:09.430 --> 02:10.762
- Really? I don't know.

02:10.764 --> 02:13.232
Maybe I should do
something with my hair.

02:13.234 --> 02:15.267
- Honey, I meant that
as a compliment.

02:15.269 --> 02:17.202
- It's just... I
wanna look good.

02:17.204 --> 02:19.404
I mean, everybody already
knows each other,

02:19.406 --> 02:22.074
and I'm gonna walk in at the
end of the school year.

02:22.076 --> 02:23.442
It's gonna be really weird.

02:23.444 --> 02:24.643
- It's gonna be great!

02:24.645 --> 02:26.812
Plus everyone's wearing
the same thing,

02:26.814 --> 02:28.280
so there's no judgement there.

02:28.282 --> 02:29.281
How about this?

02:29.283 --> 02:30.282
For your birthday,

02:30.284 --> 02:32.084
we'll go for a little
shopping spree.

02:32.086 --> 02:34.620
We'll get our hair done, our nails done.
Sound good?

02:34.622 --> 02:35.787
- Sounds great.

02:35.789 --> 02:38.557
- OK. Uh, strawberries?
Blueberries? Both?

02:38.559 --> 02:41.793
- Actually, Dad's taking me
to breakfast before class.

02:41.795 --> 02:43.428
- OK. You better get going then.

02:43.430 --> 02:44.997
- Yeah! One more thing.

02:44.999 --> 02:49.001
Could you maybe not make a
big deal about, you know,

02:49.003 --> 02:50.736
that I'm your daughter?

02:50.738 --> 02:52.404
- Of course.

02:52.406 --> 02:54.106
- You're the best!

03:07.988 --> 03:11.256
- Julie! Hi! Come on in.
- Thanks.

03:11.258 --> 03:13.759
- Have you settled
into your classroom?

03:13.761 --> 03:15.093
- Ah, that's my next stop.

03:15.095 --> 03:17.095
- Well, I know I've
said it before,

03:17.097 --> 03:19.831
but thank you for coming
in on such short notice.

03:19.833 --> 03:22.034
- I'm happy to help. I just...

03:22.036 --> 03:25.370
I wish it were under
different circumstances.

03:25.372 --> 03:27.372
- I understand you knew Joanne.

03:27.374 --> 03:28.840
- I do. We're good friends.

03:28.842 --> 03:31.310
- Well, I hope it won't
be too uncomfortable

03:31.312 --> 03:33.312
taking over her classroom.

03:33.314 --> 03:34.646
- It's a little strange,

03:34.648 --> 03:37.182
but I'm sure everyone's
feeling the same way.

03:37.184 --> 03:39.618
- You know, I worked
with Joanne for 6 years,

03:39.620 --> 03:42.221
and I never saw any sign
she would have done this.

03:42.223 --> 03:45.190
- Suicide is still
just a theory.

03:45.192 --> 03:46.625
- Of course.

03:46.627 --> 03:49.294
- How are the students
handling things?

03:49.296 --> 03:52.531
- There's been the usual
disruptions, questions.

03:52.533 --> 03:54.800
- Well, I'd love to
help in any way I can.

03:54.802 --> 03:56.835
In fact, I have an idea
for a "mindful box,"

03:56.837 --> 03:59.638
where students can express what
they're feeling anonymously.

03:59.640 --> 04:01.807
- Anything that might
help is welcome.

04:01.809 --> 04:02.808
- Great!

04:02.810 --> 04:04.409
- I'm sure I don't
need to tell you

04:04.411 --> 04:05.711
you have big shoes to fill.

04:05.713 --> 04:07.746
Joanne was strict,

04:07.748 --> 04:11.483
but teachers like her help
make Avondale one of the best.

04:11.485 --> 04:14.486
I hope you'll help us
maintain that reputation.

04:14.488 --> 04:16.321
- I will do my best.

04:39.546 --> 04:41.847
- Good morning!
- Good morning!

04:41.849 --> 04:45.384
- I heard they found a bottle
of Novaheel in Harvey's desk.

04:45.386 --> 04:48.287
- I'm not surprised.
That one had issues.

04:48.289 --> 04:50.789
- Yeah, like being an A1 bitch!

04:50.791 --> 04:53.692
- If everyone could
please take a seat,

04:53.694 --> 04:55.661
we can get started.

05:05.906 --> 05:08.874
Hi, everyone! I am Ms. Taylor.

05:08.876 --> 05:10.142
I'll be your math teacher

05:10.144 --> 05:12.044
for the remainder
of the school year.

05:12.046 --> 05:14.313
I apologize if I don't get
your names right away.

05:14.315 --> 05:16.415
It'll take me a minute,
but I will get there.

05:16.417 --> 05:19.718
I've got some good news for you.
We have a test tomorrow.

05:21.422 --> 05:24.589
- <i>Can I have your
attention, please?</i>

05:24.591 --> 05:27.726
<i>The student prom committee
is happy to announce</i>

05:27.728 --> 05:29.961
<i>this year's nominees for
prom king and queen.</i>

05:29.963 --> 05:33.098
<i>They are Tracy Pitch
and Brent Walker,</i>

05:33.100 --> 05:35.000
<i>Amy Turner and Dylan Wade...</i>

05:36.503 --> 05:39.604
<i>Heather Watts and Jack Lawson,</i>

05:39.606 --> 05:43.442
<i>and lastly, Sophie
Harris and Dave Emery.</i>

05:43.444 --> 05:44.976
What?

05:46.680 --> 05:48.313
- Well, I hope she
does something

05:48.315 --> 05:49.481
to her hair before prom.

05:51.085 --> 05:52.451
- Amy?

05:52.453 --> 05:54.653
Uh, based on your
reaction to the nominees,

05:54.655 --> 05:56.488
I'm assuming I got
your name right.

05:56.490 --> 05:57.989
- You got me.

05:57.991 --> 06:01.460
- Well, congratulations to
you and to all the nominees.

06:01.462 --> 06:03.628
- And welcome to you too, Ms.
Taylor,

06:03.630 --> 06:05.697
and your daughter.

06:05.699 --> 06:07.232
Miya, is it?

06:08.202 --> 06:09.768
- Thank you.

06:09.770 --> 06:11.837
Let's get to work, shall we?

06:11.839 --> 06:13.839
I want you to turn to page 7.

06:22.483 --> 06:25.650
- So, how was your first
morning at Avondale?

06:25.652 --> 06:27.052
- Fairly smooth!

06:27.054 --> 06:30.155
- Oh, good! I'm Aaron
Peters, 12th grade science.

06:30.157 --> 06:31.690
- Julie Taylor.
Nice to meet you.

06:31.692 --> 06:33.892
- How'd you get so lucky
to substitute here?

06:33.894 --> 06:35.894
- Oh, I'm not a
substitute, actually.

06:35.896 --> 06:38.397
I was on the tail end of a
leave when I got the call.

06:38.399 --> 06:40.065
- Oh, well, then welcome!
- Thanks!

06:40.067 --> 06:42.401
- I was just on my way to
the staffroom for lunch

06:42.403 --> 06:43.735
if you wanna meet everybody.

06:43.737 --> 06:44.970
- I'd love to, thank you.

06:44.972 --> 06:46.638
Uh, I'll be up in
a couple minutes.

06:46.640 --> 06:48.306
- All right.
- Thanks!

06:50.577 --> 06:54.045
- This one is even better.

06:54.047 --> 06:56.181
Sophie kind of looks like a dog.

06:56.183 --> 06:58.984
I'm gonna post this and
tag her as Prom Pooch.

06:58.986 --> 07:00.585
- Prom Pooch?

07:02.022 --> 07:03.121
Ah!

07:04.158 --> 07:05.490
Oh my gosh!

07:05.492 --> 07:08.460
<i>Hey, Avondale, what up?</i>

07:08.462 --> 07:12.130
<i>This is your lunchtime daily
mix from Jake, coming at ya.</i>

07:21.008 --> 07:23.275
♪♪<i> Somebody open the door</i> ♪

07:24.311 --> 07:25.610
- Hey!

07:28.949 --> 07:32.617
Does it seriously suck
starting a new school or what?

07:32.619 --> 07:33.952
- Uh, kind of.

07:33.954 --> 07:37.055
- Why don't you come sit
with me and my friends?

07:37.057 --> 07:40.659
I'll make sure it doesn't
suck nearly as bad.

07:40.661 --> 07:43.161
- OK, sure!

07:43.163 --> 07:45.831
♪ <i>I'm on the outside</i> ♪

07:45.833 --> 07:48.900
♪ <i>It's just another gold mine</i> ♪♪

07:48.902 --> 07:50.368
- You guys remember Miya.

07:50.370 --> 07:51.736
- Hey!
- Yeah, of course!

07:51.738 --> 07:53.738
- You know, I thought
he'd at least

07:53.740 --> 07:55.173
congratulate me or something.

07:55.175 --> 07:56.708
But no, he had to point out

07:56.710 --> 07:59.211
that I dropped the ball
and failed everyone,

07:59.213 --> 08:01.480
even though I haven't had
a drink in over a year.

08:01.482 --> 08:03.715
- You've gotta stop using
that word, "fail."

08:03.717 --> 08:04.816
- That's what I did.

08:04.818 --> 08:06.551
I screwed up my
marriage, my job.

08:06.553 --> 08:08.553
I almost lost custody
of my daughter.

08:08.555 --> 08:13.558
- Julie, your mom died, and
you went off the rails.

08:13.560 --> 08:16.862
As your sponsor, I can vouch
that we've all done it.

08:16.864 --> 08:20.065
But look at you now.
You're good!

08:20.067 --> 08:21.366
- I'm not gonna lie.

08:21.368 --> 08:23.935
It's... it's not easy
stepping in for Jo.

08:23.937 --> 08:26.571
I mean, I still can't
believe she...

08:26.573 --> 08:31.042
she walked out of that school
and did what they say she did.

08:31.044 --> 08:32.110
- From what I read,

08:32.111 --> 08:33.845
the evidence is
pretty compelling

08:33.847 --> 08:35.847
that she did commit suicide.

08:35.849 --> 08:37.048
- It looks like that,

08:37.049 --> 08:39.551
but I won't believe it
till they find her.

08:39.553 --> 08:40.885
Jo was tough as nails.

08:40.888 --> 08:43.188
In college, if she didn't
agree with a professor,

08:43.190 --> 08:46.124
she would outright challenge
them and not back down.

08:46.126 --> 08:49.694
- Hey, if you're
struggling at any time,

08:49.696 --> 08:51.396
you can call me, all right?

08:51.398 --> 08:54.799
- I'm pretty sure I dump
on you every chance I get.

08:54.801 --> 08:55.967
- That's true.

09:03.210 --> 09:05.043
- Hey!
- Hey!

09:05.045 --> 09:06.811
- How was your first day?

09:06.813 --> 09:09.147
- Actually, a lot
better than I thought.

09:09.149 --> 09:10.549
- Yeah? How so?

09:10.551 --> 09:13.051
- Well, you know Amy
Turner in your math class?

09:13.053 --> 09:14.152
- Yes.

09:14.154 --> 09:16.154
- Well, she asked if I could

09:16.156 --> 09:18.723
come sit with her and some
of her friends at lunch.

09:18.725 --> 09:19.891
And they are so cool!

09:19.893 --> 09:21.059
- The cool kids, huh?

09:21.061 --> 09:22.727
- Mom, don't worry.

09:22.729 --> 09:25.931
They are nothing like the girls
at Crescent, especially Amy.

09:25.933 --> 09:29.000
I mean, yes, she's popular, but
she's actually really nice.

09:29.002 --> 09:32.270
- Well, just keep your head
up and your eyes open,

09:32.272 --> 09:35.206
'cause you know how those
girls can be, right?

09:36.243 --> 09:37.776
You hungry? Indian!

09:37.778 --> 09:39.477
Sparkling water sound good?

09:39.479 --> 09:40.845
- Yeah!
- Awesome.

10:02.836 --> 10:04.169
- I'll do that!

10:04.171 --> 10:05.904
- Thanks!

10:07.374 --> 10:09.307
I gotta get to work.

10:48.649 --> 10:50.248
<i>Hey!</i>

10:50.250 --> 10:54.185
- Hey. I can't believe
Sophie Harris was nominated.

10:54.187 --> 10:56.354
<i>- She has a lot of friends, Amy.</i>

10:56.356 --> 10:58.423
- Yeah, losers!

10:58.425 --> 11:01.493
<i>- Well, there's, like, this
trend of choosing underdogs,</i>

11:01.495 --> 11:02.861
<i>like all those celebs</i>

11:02.863 --> 11:05.397
<i>who agree to go with total
geeks to their proms.</i>

11:05.399 --> 11:08.099
- Whatever. There is no
way she's gonna win.

11:08.101 --> 11:11.936
And Heather and Tracy, like,
they're not even in the running.

11:11.938 --> 11:14.673
Look, I gotta go. I'll
talk to you later.

11:45.205 --> 11:48.306
- Wow! Didn't realize
Joanne had so many haters.

11:48.308 --> 11:51.609
- Well, they'll realize
eventually the toughest teachers

11:51.611 --> 11:53.044
are often the best ones.

11:58.885 --> 12:02.287
- Do you seriously think you
have a chance at winning?

12:02.289 --> 12:03.955
- If I don't, then
why do you care?

12:03.957 --> 12:05.724
- Maybe I'm trying
to do you a favour

12:05.726 --> 12:07.592
so you don't look
like a loser at prom.

12:07.594 --> 12:09.461
Either way, you better drop out.

12:09.463 --> 12:13.231
That crown's not gonna look very
good if you don't have any hair!

12:13.233 --> 12:14.532
- Girls!

12:15.669 --> 12:17.402
Is there a problem?

12:17.404 --> 12:19.037
- I've gotta get to class.

12:20.607 --> 12:23.441
- You know, I don't know why
she doesn't take my advice

12:23.443 --> 12:25.744
and style her hair
in an updo for prom.

12:25.746 --> 12:27.112
It would look amazing!

12:27.114 --> 12:29.781
- So, that's what this was
about, hairstyling tips?

12:29.783 --> 12:33.184
Because from where I stood,
it didn't look so innocent.

12:33.186 --> 12:34.419
- Really?

12:34.421 --> 12:36.788
Well, I can tell you,
anyone at this school

12:36.790 --> 12:40.592
would die to have Amy Turner
give them beauty advice.

12:40.594 --> 12:42.260
- And why is that?

12:42.262 --> 12:44.129
- Because I'm just that popular.

12:44.131 --> 12:46.798
Your daughter's really
lucky to be my friend.

12:46.800 --> 12:49.601
- I think you should
probably head to class.

12:52.272 --> 12:53.738
Oh, and, Amy...

12:54.708 --> 12:56.608
I'm watching you.

13:07.621 --> 13:10.288
Eyes on your test, please.

13:13.827 --> 13:16.027
- <i>Sorry for the interruption.</i>

13:16.029 --> 13:18.329
<i>Just a brief announcement
that Sophie Harris</i>

13:18.331 --> 13:20.965
<i>has withdrawn her name as
nominee for prom queen.</i>

13:20.967 --> 13:24.669
<i>Ballots will be accepted
until the end of next week</i>

13:24.671 --> 13:26.070
<i>for a new nomination.</i>

13:26.072 --> 13:28.306
<i>Thank you.</i>

13:30.310 --> 13:31.676
All right, time's up!

13:31.678 --> 13:33.678
Everyone, have a great weekend!

13:33.680 --> 13:38.183
Reminder: Chapter 12, Questions
1 through 8 are due on Monday.

13:38.185 --> 13:39.884
Thank you!

13:41.855 --> 13:43.321
- Hey!

13:47.227 --> 13:49.627
- Thank you. Thank you!

13:51.598 --> 13:53.364
Sophie, you have a minute?

13:53.366 --> 13:55.233
What happened?

13:55.235 --> 13:57.735
Why did you remove your
name from the nominee list?

13:57.737 --> 13:59.270
- It's just not worth it.

13:59.272 --> 14:00.605
- What do you mean?

14:00.607 --> 14:02.006
- To go up against Amy.

14:02.008 --> 14:04.409
- Well, everyone has a
chance at winning, Sophie.

14:04.411 --> 14:05.410
- You don't get it.

14:05.412 --> 14:06.845
I just wanna finish school

14:06.847 --> 14:08.479
and not have to deal with her.

14:56.162 --> 14:59.764
- I just rescued this from
being used as a football.

14:59.766 --> 15:01.332
- Thank you.

15:01.334 --> 15:03.768
- You know, the staff
should have one of those,

15:03.770 --> 15:05.503
so we can bitch
about how this job

15:05.505 --> 15:07.405
can suck the life
right out of you.

15:07.407 --> 15:08.606
- So you've lost optimism

15:08.608 --> 15:10.642
that we're making the
world a better place

15:10.644 --> 15:11.676
one student at a time?

15:11.678 --> 15:13.311
- Have you met some
of these kids?

15:13.313 --> 15:14.445
- I have!

15:14.447 --> 15:16.281
Actually, there's
one in particular

15:16.283 --> 15:18.516
who strikes me as a
bit of a life-sucker.

15:18.518 --> 15:20.351
- Oh, let me guess. Amy Turner?

15:20.353 --> 15:21.986
- So she has a reputation.

15:21.988 --> 15:23.821
- Oh yeah! Amy's one of a kind.

15:23.823 --> 15:26.658
She's smart, and she knows
how to get under your skin.

15:26.660 --> 15:28.860
So, if I were you, I'd
stay out of her way,

15:28.862 --> 15:31.029
or your time here at
Avondale may be over

15:31.031 --> 15:33.064
before it's even begun.

16:03.063 --> 16:04.829
Hey, Mom!

16:04.831 --> 16:07.398
- Hey! You wanna go out
for dinner tonight?

16:07.400 --> 16:10.234
- Actually, Amy invited
me to hang out with her

16:10.236 --> 16:11.669
and some of her friends.

16:11.671 --> 16:12.971
- Oh, OK!

16:12.973 --> 16:16.307
- So can we skip dinner
tonight, if that's OK?

16:16.309 --> 16:18.042
- We'll be ordering pizza.

16:18.044 --> 16:19.844
- Sure.

16:19.846 --> 16:21.779
- All right! Great!
I'm gonna go change.

16:23.316 --> 16:26.150
- So, where are you two planning
on hanging out tonight?

16:26.152 --> 16:27.385
- Uh, at my boyfriend's.

16:27.387 --> 16:30.054
Don't worry, his
parents are fine

16:30.056 --> 16:33.391
with having people over
when they're away.

16:33.393 --> 16:36.327
Where's Mr. Taylor?
Working late?

16:36.329 --> 16:38.763
- Miya's father and
I are separated.

16:38.765 --> 16:41.399
- My dad's not around either.

16:41.401 --> 16:43.001
- Mark's around.

16:43.003 --> 16:46.104
- Whatever keeps the
support cheques coming.

16:46.106 --> 16:48.840
My mom and I didn't
get that luxury.

16:48.842 --> 16:52.343
- So, how are you adjusting
with the changes at the school?

16:52.345 --> 16:56.280
- If you're talking about Harvey
killing herself, it's too bad.

16:56.282 --> 16:57.682
But I'm fine with it,

16:57.684 --> 17:00.785
because, to be honest,
no one really liked her.

17:00.787 --> 17:03.855
- I'm asking because I
just graded your test,

17:03.857 --> 17:07.191
and the results are
less than spectacular.

17:07.193 --> 17:10.627
- So? There's only a few
weeks of school left.

17:10.630 --> 17:12.063
No big deal, right?

17:12.065 --> 17:15.233
- Well, it is a big deal.
I'm your teacher.

17:17.203 --> 17:19.369
- Does it make your
job more fulfilling

17:19.372 --> 17:21.039
if your students like you?

17:21.040 --> 17:24.942
- No. Teaching isn't a
popularity contest.

17:24.944 --> 17:27.545
- But it would make
things easier.

17:28.815 --> 17:30.314
Like for Joanne,

17:30.316 --> 17:32.784
if she hadn't tried to
play by all the rules.

17:32.786 --> 17:34.152
But she didn't get that

17:34.154 --> 17:36.888
that's not how things
are run at our school.

17:36.890 --> 17:38.389
- How are things run?

17:39.492 --> 17:41.626
- You'll figure it out.

17:42.929 --> 17:44.829
Wow, you look hot!

17:44.831 --> 17:47.265
- Thanks! So, I'll see you?

17:47.267 --> 17:49.067
- Have fun. Home
by midnight, OK?

17:49.069 --> 17:50.401
- OK.

17:51.604 --> 17:53.438
- I wonder if Sara's
gonna be there.

17:53.440 --> 17:58.242
You know she got asked out
by this guy in college.

17:58.244 --> 17:59.677
- How do you just, like,

17:59.679 --> 18:02.013
walk out your door one day
and jump into a river?

18:02.015 --> 18:04.348
- They don't know if that's
exactly what she did.

18:04.350 --> 18:05.750
- What else could've happened?

18:05.752 --> 18:07.618
- I don't know. They
don't have a body.

18:07.620 --> 18:10.354
- I heard the last person
who saw her was Mr. Peters.

18:10.356 --> 18:12.723
- Oh, so you think he has
something to do with it?

18:12.725 --> 18:14.058
- It is weird.

18:14.060 --> 18:17.028
- Maybe he's always wanted
to dissect a cadaver.

18:17.030 --> 18:20.264
- Or maybe he's, like, a
closet serial killer.

18:20.266 --> 18:22.533
- Who?
- Mr. Peters.

18:22.535 --> 18:24.769
We're thinking he has Ms.
Harvey's body

