have to do with me?

37:45.464 --> 37:49.733
- Well, I was hoping that you
could get me a copy of the test

37:49.735 --> 37:51.568
that I can use to study,

37:51.570 --> 37:54.337
and I won't tell
anyone about that time

37:54.339 --> 37:56.673
that you put your
hand up my skirt.

37:56.675 --> 37:58.508
- Well, that never happened.

37:58.510 --> 37:59.509
- Didn't it?

37:59.511 --> 38:01.511
Because I'm sure that the board

38:01.513 --> 38:03.747
could easily be
convinced otherwise.

38:03.749 --> 38:07.284
And I know that you wanna just
finish out the school year

38:07.286 --> 38:08.718
with a good reputation.

38:15.260 --> 38:17.193
- Miya, your father's here!

38:18.897 --> 38:20.764
Hey! You wanna come in?

38:20.766 --> 38:24.467
- Actually, uh, I was hoping
to have a word. Outside?

38:24.469 --> 38:26.269
- OK.

38:28.974 --> 38:30.640
What is it?

38:30.642 --> 38:33.710
- I got a call late last
night from your sponsor.

38:33.712 --> 38:35.345
She said you had a relapse.

38:36.581 --> 38:38.515
- That's impossible.

38:39.484 --> 38:40.917
That's not true!

38:40.919 --> 38:42.986
- Look, I know you've
had a hard time

38:42.988 --> 38:44.988
with this whole Joanne thing,

38:44.990 --> 38:47.490
but the only reason
you won joint custody

38:47.492 --> 38:49.159
was because you were sober.

38:49.161 --> 38:50.660
But that all can change.

38:50.662 --> 38:53.496
- Mark, I haven't had a
drink in almost 13 months.

38:53.498 --> 38:57.400
Kate knows that! She wouldn't
say anything differently.

38:57.402 --> 38:59.736
Call her! Call my
sponsor, Mark, please!

38:59.738 --> 39:01.004
- What's going on?

39:01.006 --> 39:02.972
- Your father thinks
I've been drinking.

39:02.974 --> 39:05.575
- Dad, she hasn't. Trust
me, I know she hasn't.

39:05.577 --> 39:08.745
- We should go. I only get a few
hours with my birthday girl.

39:08.747 --> 39:11.314
- Mark, I am telling
you the truth!

39:20.158 --> 39:21.324
-<i> Hello!</i>

39:21.326 --> 39:23.426
- Kate, it's Julie.
- <i>Hey!</i>

39:23.428 --> 39:24.861
- What's going on?

39:24.863 --> 39:26.796
-<i> What? What do you mean?</i>

39:26.798 --> 39:28.865
- Uh, Mark said you
left him a message

39:28.867 --> 39:30.633
saying I've been drinking again.

39:30.635 --> 39:35.171
- What? Why would I do that?
I've never called Mark.

39:35.173 --> 39:37.540
- Well, why would he
just make that up?

39:37.542 --> 39:40.510
- Julie, I didn't
call your ex-husband.

39:40.512 --> 39:42.379
<i>For one, I don't
have his number.</i>

39:42.381 --> 39:44.881
<i>And secondly, I know you
haven't been drinking.</i>

39:44.883 --> 39:46.783
So it wasn't me.

39:46.785 --> 39:48.685
- OK.

39:54.359 --> 39:56.693
- She thinks.

39:56.695 --> 39:59.028
She thinks she's
doing me a favour.

39:59.030 --> 40:00.597
But she doesn't get it!

40:00.599 --> 40:04.100
You don't threaten me, Ms.
Taylor!

40:04.102 --> 40:07.604
I think we all know how
that's gonna end, Joanne.

40:07.606 --> 40:10.373
I don't want your friend
to end up like you.

40:14.012 --> 40:15.512
Do it.

40:18.683 --> 40:22.152
Do it! And make sure
you show your work.

40:29.861 --> 40:33.163
You know, no adult has
ever been in here...

40:35.100 --> 40:36.900
not even my mom.

40:38.703 --> 40:41.738
Because you were only
allowed in if I said so.

40:43.408 --> 40:45.675
Not that I had any friends.

40:48.213 --> 40:52.649
They made fun of
me for my clothes,

40:52.651 --> 40:55.051
for my $10 haircut.

40:57.055 --> 41:01.691
And Meg Dyer, she was the worst.

41:03.295 --> 41:06.129
That fat bitch!

41:08.133 --> 41:09.732
So, one day,

41:09.734 --> 41:12.836
I told her that I had all this
Halloween candy to give her,

41:12.838 --> 41:14.904
and I brought her back here.

41:20.579 --> 41:22.345
But there was no candy.

41:26.585 --> 41:27.917
After that...

41:29.488 --> 41:31.654
she never bullied me again.

41:32.858 --> 41:35.892
No one ever did.

41:39.698 --> 41:41.297
- Hmm...

41:49.007 --> 41:51.374
- What are you gonna do, Joanne?

41:51.376 --> 41:52.842
Stab me with it?

41:52.844 --> 41:56.412
It's gonna take a lot more
than a pencil to hurt me.

42:12.898 --> 42:16.032
You might actually
prove to be useful.

42:22.340 --> 42:24.440
- Julie, can I talk to you?

42:25.577 --> 42:27.644
It'll just take a second.

42:30.715 --> 42:32.048
- What is it?

42:32.050 --> 42:34.517
- Well, I wanted to get
your opinion on something

42:34.519 --> 42:36.252
before I meet with
a student of mine.

42:36.254 --> 42:37.720
- Couldn't this wait?

42:37.722 --> 42:40.723
- Sure, but I... I... I was
worried I was gonna miss you,

42:40.725 --> 42:43.259
um, and I'm gonna meet
him just before lunch.

42:43.261 --> 42:45.995
- OK, well, I'll make sure
to find you before lunch.

42:59.244 --> 43:02.545
- Vote for Amy Turner
and Dylan Wade

43:02.547 --> 43:05.848
for this year's prom
king and queen!

43:05.850 --> 43:07.951
And in case anyone has forgotten

43:07.953 --> 43:11.621
how we have represented the
school for the last 4 years,

43:11.623 --> 43:13.356
here's a little cheat sheet

43:13.358 --> 43:17.226
to remind you of why we deserve
to be your prom king and queen.

43:17.228 --> 43:19.095
- Does it have "stud" on there?

43:19.097 --> 43:20.229
- Shut up!

43:20.231 --> 43:22.265
- Seriously, we're
Avondale royalty!

43:41.920 --> 43:44.787
- So, what did you wanna
talk to me about?

43:44.789 --> 43:46.122
- It's Amy's marks.

43:46.124 --> 43:48.725
Based on the grade she
received from Ms. Harvey

43:48.727 --> 43:50.259
and the test she just retook,

43:50.261 --> 43:52.061
it looks like she's
failing math.

43:52.063 --> 43:53.730
- Really? I'm surprised.

43:53.732 --> 43:56.332
Amy's marks have
always been so good.

43:56.334 --> 43:59.936
- Well, it doesn't look like
this is working out for her.

43:59.938 --> 44:02.705
And if she doesn't pass,
she won't graduate.

44:03.842 --> 44:06.776
- I wasn't aware of any of this.

44:06.778 --> 44:10.246
- Ms. Harvey never spoke
with you about Amy's grades?

44:10.248 --> 44:12.915
- She called, and we were
planning on meeting,

44:12.917 --> 44:16.085
but then a few days later,
I heard she disappeared.

44:19.691 --> 44:21.491
Amy, sweetie!

44:21.493 --> 44:24.594
Your teacher dropped by
to discuss your marks.

44:26.131 --> 44:29.065
- You failed your test again.

44:34.039 --> 44:36.105
- That's not possible.

44:37.142 --> 44:38.941
- I have it right here.

44:43.014 --> 44:44.647
- I'm sure that there's a way

44:44.649 --> 44:47.150
that she could retake
it again, right?

44:47.152 --> 44:49.819
- Actually, I was already
stretching the rules

44:49.821 --> 44:51.521
by giving her another chance.

44:51.523 --> 44:53.623
- What about the
final assignment?

44:53.625 --> 44:55.058
That's worth 20%, right?

44:55.060 --> 44:57.293
- It is, but you'd
have to score a 98%

44:57.295 --> 44:59.328
to bring your grade
just above a pass.

44:59.330 --> 45:00.363
- I'll do it.

45:00.365 --> 45:02.331
- I appreciate the intent,

45:02.333 --> 45:05.468
but I think we need to be
realistic based on your year.

45:05.470 --> 45:08.137
- You don't know me well
enough to assume anything.

45:08.139 --> 45:11.574
- OK, I'm sure that Amy will
do whatever she has to do

45:11.576 --> 45:13.009
to bring up her mark.

45:13.011 --> 45:14.877
- I'm sure she will.

45:16.715 --> 45:18.581
Thank you for your time, Elaine.

45:18.583 --> 45:21.718
You have my cell if you need
to discuss anything further.

45:21.720 --> 45:23.286
Thank you.

45:32.497 --> 45:34.230
- Why didn't you do something?

45:34.232 --> 45:36.032
- What did you expect me to do?

45:36.034 --> 45:39.335
- Oh my God! That bitch is
trying to ruin everything!

45:39.337 --> 45:43.272
- Amy! Where are you going?

45:55.386 --> 45:58.554
- What the hell do you
think you're doing?

45:58.556 --> 46:00.757
- You got your test back.

46:02.293 --> 46:05.895
- Do you see where
you are right now?

46:05.897 --> 46:08.564
You don't get to play
teacher anymore!

46:08.566 --> 46:12.235
If you don't help me pass,
I swear I will kill you.

46:12.237 --> 46:15.104
- Wasn't that your plan anyhow?

46:15.106 --> 46:17.039
Or do you have a plan?

47:29.781 --> 47:31.480
I mean, she's only
been at school

47:31.482 --> 47:33.449
for what, like, 2 weeks?

47:33.451 --> 47:34.984
- Whatever, I'm not worried.

47:34.986 --> 47:38.120
- Do you imagine how much it
would suck if she were your mom?

47:38.122 --> 47:40.356
- Well, maybe Miya gets
perks because of it.

47:40.358 --> 47:41.824
- I don't think she bends.

47:41.826 --> 47:44.193
- Hey!
- Hey.

47:44.195 --> 47:47.430
- What were you
guys talking about?

47:47.432 --> 47:50.633
- How cool it would be if
your mom was your teacher.

47:50.635 --> 47:53.169
I mean, there's no way that
you could fail, right?

47:53.171 --> 47:56.005
- My mom wouldn't
give me a free pass.

47:56.007 --> 47:58.841
- Well, that sucks. We'll
talk to you later.

48:03.147 --> 48:04.947
- You OK?

48:04.949 --> 48:06.682
- Yeah, I'm fine.

48:06.684 --> 48:08.451
- Do you wanna hang
out after school

48:08.453 --> 48:09.785
and go over some prom stuff?

48:09.787 --> 48:11.120
- Sure.

48:11.122 --> 48:12.655
- Can we do it at your place?

48:12.657 --> 48:15.558
My mom's working nights, and
she hates to be woken up.

48:15.560 --> 48:17.159
- Yeah, no problem!

48:17.161 --> 48:20.263
- Cool! I'll see you
after school then.

48:35.046 --> 48:36.812
- What are you doing?

48:36.814 --> 48:40.750
- My dress is in desperate need
of some extra bling for prom.

48:40.752 --> 48:43.619
I thought maybe your mom
would have something.

48:44.822 --> 48:46.522
Come on! We're just trying it.

48:46.524 --> 48:48.090
We'll put it back.

48:48.092 --> 48:52.528
- OK. My mom does have a few
things my dad gave her.

48:53.531 --> 48:55.965
Let's see...

48:57.435 --> 49:01.237
- Do you have a dress yet?
- Uh, no, not yet.

49:06.945 --> 49:09.745
You should wear your
hair up for prom.

49:09.747 --> 49:12.415
It would look amazing.

49:14.218 --> 49:16.352
- What about these?

49:16.354 --> 49:18.654
- Ah, yes! They're perfect.

49:21.960 --> 49:24.093
Oh, I dropped one.

49:25.263 --> 49:26.929
I can't see where it went.

49:26.931 --> 49:28.030
- Really?

49:29.434 --> 49:31.200
- Maybe it went under the bed.

49:36.474 --> 49:37.606
- Did you find it?

49:39.711 --> 49:41.177
- Yeah.

49:43.448 --> 49:46.082
- You look like you saw a ghost.

49:46.084 --> 49:49.085
- Hey, let's just
put these back.

50:52.950 --> 50:55.918
I thought about it,
and you deserve this.

50:57.321 --> 50:59.522
What's wrong? What is going on?

50:59.524 --> 51:01.957
- Found this beside your bed.

51:01.959 --> 51:05.327
- Miya, this isn't mine.
- Don't lie to me!

51:05.329 --> 51:07.863
- It's... it's not!
- Then where did it come from?

51:07.865 --> 51:09.965
You're the only one in
the house who drinks.

51:09.967 --> 51:11.500
- I don't drink, Miya!

51:11.502 --> 51:14.203
- Bull! I backed you with
Dad, and you were lying!

51:14.205 --> 51:16.705
So how am I supposed
to talk to you now

51:16.707 --> 51:18.707
if you weren't even
honest with me?

51:18.709 --> 51:20.176
- Miya, please...
- No! No.

51:20.178 --> 51:21.877
- Please.
- No! You know what?

51:21.879 --> 51:24.547
You said this was gonna be a
fresh start for both of us,

51:24.549 --> 51:26.382
and I was finally
starting to feel good.

51:26.384 --> 51:29.185
I mean, what would I have
said if Amy found this?

51:29.187 --> 51:30.252
- Amy was here?

51:30.254 --> 51:31.554
- We were planning prom!

51:31.556 --> 51:32.855
- Were you in my room?

51:32.857 --> 51:34.390
- What does that have to do...

51:34.392 --> 51:36.058
- Were you in my room?

51:36.060 --> 51:37.426
- Why are you yelling at me?

51:37.428 --> 51:39.728
- I don't trust her! I
don't trust that girl!

51:39.730 --> 51:41.430
- Seriously? You're blaming Amy?

51:41.432 --> 51:42.865
- Miya, I am not the only one.

51:42.867 --> 51:45.000
Teachers have left the
school because of her.

51:45.002 --> 51:47.503
- I don't believe you!

51:49.006 --> 51:52.842
- You know I don't drink.
You know I don't!

51:52.844 --> 51:54.176
Where are you going?

51:54.178 --> 51:55.511
- I'm going to Dad's.

51:55.513 --> 51:57.179
Don't worry, I won't
tell him why.

51:57.181 --> 51:58.948
I won't as long as
you don't stop me.

51:58.950 --> 52:00.549
- Miya!

52:53.271 --> 52:54.803
- Amy...

52:54.805 --> 52:57.573
- Not right now, Mom. I'm
gonna be late for school.

53:02.079 --> 53:04.413
- <i>Good morning, Avondale!</i>

53:04.415 --> 53:05.948
<i>With prom just 3 days away,</i>

53:05.950 --> 53:08.450
<i>members, don't miss
the committee meeting</i>

53:08.452 --> 53:11.020
<i>today during lunch
in the library.</i>

53:11.022 --> 53:13.856
- We should rent
a limo for prom.

53:13.858 --> 53:15.858
- A white one with a sun roof.

53:15.860 --> 53:17.526
- Ooh!

53:17.528 --> 53:19.128
- You know, I've been thinking,

53:19.130 --> 53:22.164
isn't it kind of cramping our
style hanging out with Miya?

53:22.166 --> 53:24.934
She's nice or whatever, but
her mom is such a bitch!

53:24.936 --> 53:26.202
- To you, she is.

53:26.204 --> 53:29.471
- Well, Miya has done
nothing to back me.

53:29.473 --> 53:33.676
- So, should we get a
stretch or a stacked SUV?

53:33.678 --> 53:36.679
- You guys thinking of
renting a limo for prom?

53:36.681 --> 53:40.115
- Of course!
- Cool! I'd be into that!

53:40.117 --> 53:43.185
- Don't you have to be
there early or something

53:43.187 --> 53:44.853
for committee?

53:44.855 --> 53:47.489
Maybe you could just
go on your own.

53:48.526 --> 53:49.858
- Ah!

54:04.976 --> 54:08.544
- How dare you try to manipulate
my daughter and my life!

54:08.546 --> 54:11.313
- Honestly, I don't what
you are on about now.

54:11.315 --> 54:15.484
- I know you ended Ms. Saunders'
marriage and pushed her out.

54:15.486 --> 54:17.386
I am not going anywhere!

54:18.923 --> 54:22.024
- That's fine. I
like a challenge.

54:22.026 --> 54:23.892
And you know what they say!

54:23.894 --> 54:27.162
Every hurdle you knock over
just makes you stronger.

54:27.164 --> 54:29.665
- It's every hurdle
you overcome, Amy.

54:29.667 --> 54:33.902
You are not as smart as you
lie and cheat and pretend...

54:33.904 --> 54:35.371
- Actually, I am.

54:35.373 --> 54:38.207
'Cause if you look at the
assignment I'm handing in,

54:38.209 --> 54:39.775
you'll see that it's perfect,

54:39.777 --> 54:42.411
which raises my grade
just over a pass.

54:42.413 --> 54:44.413
So go ahead.

54:45.683 --> 54:48.617
Stick around! I've won!

54:48.619 --> 54:51.553
There's nothing more
that you can do.

55:19.116 --> 55:20.249
Psst!

55:46.577 --> 55:48.410
- Miya. Miya!

56:54.078 --> 56:56.078
- What are you doing?

56:56.080 --> 56:58.180
- Just collecting laundry.

56:58.182 --> 56:59.381
- I can do it.

56:59.383 --> 57:01.650
- You're gonna wanna put
stain spray on that.

57:01.652 --> 57:03.385
What happened? Did
you cut yourself?

57:03.387 --> 57:04.553
- At school.

57:04.555 --> 57:06.588
- Well, here, let me
take a look at it!

57:06.590 --> 57:09.358
- It's fine! God, just
go play nurse at work!

57:57.808 --> 57:59.641
- You looking for these?

57:59.643 --> 58:02.277
You've become a lot
of things, Amy,

58:02.279 --> 58:04.780
but I didn't think
you'd turn to this.

58:04.782 --> 58:06.615
- I'm not a pill popper, Mom.

58:06.617 --> 58:08.617
- Then where have they gone?

58:08.619 --> 58:11.920
- I don't know. Maybe you took
them and you don't even know it?

58:11.922 --> 58:14.423
I see you popping them
like candy with your wine.

58:14.425 --> 58:16.225
- That's not true. You know it.

58:16.227 --> 58:20.095
- Isn't it? Whose name
is on the bottle, Mom?

58:20.097 --> 58:22.831
Why? Why do you even take them?

58:22.833 --> 58:24.132
- This isn't about me.

58:24.134 --> 58:26.635
- Of course it is, because
if I were taking them,

58:26.637 --> 58:27.936
whose fault would that be?

58:27.938 --> 58:29.605
Who brought them
into this house?

58:29.607 --> 58:31.006
- You're turning this around!

58:31.008 --> 58:34.076
- Yeah, because you won't
answer the question.

58:34.078 --> 58:35.744
Why? Why do you take them?

58:35.746 --> 58:38.614
Is it because your
job is too stressful

58:38.616 --> 58:40.482
or because Dad left us?

58:40.484 --> 58:42.251
Or maybe it's all those things,

58:42.253 --> 58:44.253
because your sad,
pathetic, little life

58:44.255 --> 58:46.021
didn't turn out the
way you planned,

58:46.023 --> 58:47.589
working 12-hour shifts

58:47.591 --> 58:50.526
with no one to come home to but
your bottle and your pills.

58:50.528 --> 58:52.661
- It's you, all right?

58:53.764 --> 58:56.298
I take them because of you.

58:57.768 --> 59:01.770
- Well, in a couple of
months, I'll be gone,

59:01.772 --> 59:04.740
and then you can have
them all to yourself.

01:00:09.540 --> 01:00:11.573
Are you following me?

01:00:11.575 --> 01:00:14.409
- I did say I was watching you.

01:00:17.448 --> 01:00:21.550
- You have no idea the
mistake that you just made.

01:00:23.053 --> 01:00:24.953
- Tell me something, Amy.

01:00:24.955 --> 01:00:29.825
Why do your handwritten
numbers match Joanne's?

01:00:32.763 --> 01:00:34.896
- Are you serious?

01:00:34.898 --> 01:00:36.365
- Very.

01:00:38.135 --> 01:00:40.535
- You're crazier
than your friend.

01:00:40.537 --> 01:00:41.737
- I don't think so.

01:00:41.739 --> 01:00:43.739
In fact, I think the
detective on the case

01:00:43.741 --> 01:00:45.240
will call this evidence.

01:00:45.242 --> 01:00:48.644
- And I'm pretty sure that he
would call this harassment.

01:00:48.646 --> 01:00:51.480
Following a student,
accusing them of nothing?

01:00:51.482 --> 01:00:54.816
- You know, you can spin
this however you want, Amy,

01:00:54.818 --> 01:00:56.985
but I haven't done
anything wrong.

01:00:56.987 --> 01:01:00.789
I'm out on a walk, and I
happened to run into you.

01:01:00.791 --> 01:01:04.459
- Oh. OK, so, I'm not here.

01:01:04.461 --> 01:01:06.128
I'm at home.

01:01:07.598 --> 01:01:09.131
What's that?

01:01:09.133 --> 01:01:10.966
My teacher's at my door.

01:01:10.968 --> 01:01:14.269
She's accusing me of
having something to do

01:01:14.271 --> 01:01:16.471
with her daughter moving out.

01:01:16.473 --> 01:01:21.343
She's really angry, and I'm
pretty sure she's drunk.

01:01:21.345 --> 01:01:22.644
I'm just guessing,

01:01:22.646 --> 01:01:24.846
but maybe she fell off the wagon

01:01:24.848 --> 01:01:27.149
because of her dear
friend Joanne.

01:01:28.652 --> 01:01:30.986
And when I try to
get her to leave,

01:01:30.988 --> 01:01:32.721
she lashes out...

01:01:34.091 --> 01:01:35.657
and she hits me.

01:01:36.827 --> 01:01:38.226
- Great story.

01:01:39.196 --> 01:01:40.796
No one will believe it.

01:01:40.798 --> 01:01:42.197
- You don't think so?

01:01:42.199 --> 01:01:43.665
- I don't think so.

01:01:50.174 --> 01:01:51.440
- Ah!

01:01:56.447 --> 01:01:58.013
No, don't!

01:01:58.015 --> 01:01:59.781
- Amy, stop it!

01:02:02.519 --> 01:02:03.852
What the hell?

01:02:06.023 --> 01:02:08.356
- Ms. Taylor, please!

01:02:34.318 --> 01:02:37.486
- I know how uncomfortable
this must be for you, Amy.

01:02:37.488 --> 01:02:40.355
And I'm sure Ms. Taylor
appreciates your understanding

01:02:40.357 --> 01:02:41.823
as much as I do.

01:02:41.825 --> 01:02:44.259
- Vicky, with all due
respect, this didn't happen.

01:02:44.261 --> 01:02:45.694
None of it.

01:02:45.696 --> 01:02:48.597
In my whole life, I have never
laid my hand on anyone,

01:02:48.599 --> 01:02:49.598
let alone a student.

01:02:49.600 --> 01:02:50.899
I mean, to even suggest...

01:02:50.901 --> 01:02:53.201
- Ms. Taylor, Amy has
been generous enough

01:02:53.203 --> 01:02:56.004
for not filing a
formal complaint.

01:02:56.006 --> 01:02:58.073
Her request that you be
dismissed immediately

01:02:58.075 --> 01:02:59.074
is not uncalled for.

01:02:59.076 --> 01:03:00.509
- Please.

01:03:01.678 --> 01:03:02.844
Elaine...

01:03:03.914 --> 01:03:05.447
We all know our children.

01:03:05.449 --> 01:03:07.582
And that's our
responsibility as parents

01:03:07.584 --> 01:03:10.051
is to know our children.

01:03:11.288 --> 01:03:13.922
And you let her get
away with this,

01:03:13.924 --> 01:03:17.759
you're letting her get away
with a pretty big lie.

01:03:19.129 --> 01:03:21.429
I... I... I wanted
to talk to her.

01:03:21.431 --> 01:03:22.864
I saw her...

01:03:22.866 --> 01:03:25.801
I saw her walk behind the
house and into the woods,

01:03:25.803 --> 01:03:27.269
and I followed her.

01:03:27.271 --> 01:03:28.537
- Can we please go now?

01:03:28.539 --> 01:03:30.305
- Of course.

01:03:30.307 --> 01:03:33.642
- She left this stuck to
my door with a knife.

01:03:33.644 --> 01:03:35.877
- You saw her do this?
- I didn't see her. I...

01:03:35.879 --> 01:03:38.747
I know it was her, because she's
been doing stuff like this.

01:03:38.749 --> 01:03:40.949
She's been bullying me
since I started this job,

01:03:40.951 --> 01:03:41.950
and I... I won't cave!

01:03:41.952 --> 01:03:44.219
- Julie, that's enough!

01:03:44.221 --> 01:03:45.987
On behalf of the entire school,

01:03:45.989 --> 01:03:47.956
you have our sincerest apologies

01:03:47.958 --> 01:03:50.258
and assurance this
will be dealt with.

01:03:59.269 --> 01:04:00.936
What the hell was that about?

01:04:00.938 --> 01:04:03.271
- You don't get it! She's crazy!

01:04:03.273 --> 01:04:06.408
I mean, she... Vicky, you gotta
believe me, she did this.

01:04:06.410 --> 01:04:08.910
She did this. She did
that to her face.

01:04:08.912 --> 01:04:11.513
- So, what? An 18-year-old
was bullying you?

01:04:11.515 --> 01:04:12.948
- She's manipulative.

01:04:12.950 --> 01:04:15.450
I mean, she knows what to
do to get what she wants.

01:04:15.452 --> 01:04:17.452
I mean, you can ask
Mr. Peters, ask Carol.

01:04:17.454 --> 01:04:18.653
- I don't have to, Julie.

01:04:18.655 --> 01:04:20.789
There's never been a
complaint against her.

01:04:20.791 --> 01:04:22.524
- No one wants to
lose their job!

01:04:22.526 --> 01:04:24.292
- OK, we're done here.

01:04:27.030 --> 01:04:30.065
And, Julie, get some help.

01:04:52.689 --> 01:04:54.256
- Amy!

01:05:44.441 --> 01:05:45.674
- Hi!

01:05:45.676 --> 01:05:47.175
- Hi!

01:05:47.177 --> 01:05:48.610
I'm sorry. Uh, did you call?

01:05:48.612 --> 01:05:50.145
Because my phone didn't ring.

01:05:50.147 --> 01:05:53.448
- No, um, I have Miya's prom dress.
Is she home?

01:05:53.450 --> 01:05:56.017
- Yeah, she just got
back from school.

01:05:56.019 --> 01:05:57.953
Um, come on in.

01:06:00.857 --> 01:06:02.657
Miya!

01:06:14.004 --> 01:06:15.337
- Hey!

01:06:15.339 --> 01:06:16.871
- Hey.

01:06:16.873 --> 01:06:19.474
- What are you doing here?

01:06:19.476 --> 01:06:20.976
- I brought your prom dress.

01:06:20.978 --> 01:06:23.545
You don't have to wear it,
but I know you love it,

01:06:23.547 --> 01:06:25.380
and I wanted you to
have the option.

01:06:25.382 --> 01:06:28.216
- Thank you.
- Sure.

01:06:28.218 --> 01:06:31.152
- How about I, uh, put that
up in your room for you?

01:06:31.154 --> 01:06:32.620
Thanks.

01:06:48.171 --> 01:06:50.372
I wanted to let you know

01:06:50.374 --> 01:06:53.408
that it didn't... Didn't
work out at school.

01:06:53.410 --> 01:06:56.111
But I figure that gives us a...
a chance

01:06:56.113 --> 01:06:58.179
for a fresh start
somewhere else, right?

01:06:58.181 --> 01:06:59.581
- Another fresh start.

01:06:59.583 --> 01:07:01.883
- I know you don't have a
lot of faith in me now,

01:07:01.885 --> 01:07:04.519
but don't believe
everything you hear.

01:07:04.521 --> 01:07:06.354
- What are you talking about?

01:07:06.356 --> 01:07:08.256
- You know me, Miya.

01:07:08.258 --> 01:07:10.425
Please don't forget that, OK?

01:07:11.728 --> 01:07:13.228
And I love you.

01:07:13.230 --> 01:07:17.032
So I want you to have a
great time at prom tonight,

01:07:17.034 --> 01:07:19.601
and stay away from Amy.

01:07:22.706 --> 01:07:24.439
Have fun.

01:07:54.337 --> 01:07:55.970
- Mom!

01:07:58.708 --> 01:08:00.241
Mom!

01:08:04.381 --> 01:08:05.847
Mom!

01:08:08.185 --> 01:08:10.185
Can you zip me up, please?

01:08:15.525 --> 01:08:17.258
- I saw you...

01:08:18.328 --> 01:08:20.528
going into the woods.

01:08:21.564 --> 01:08:23.531
What were you doing?

01:08:25.068 --> 01:08:27.035
- I'm 18, Mother.

01:08:28.505 --> 01:08:31.473
I don't have to tell you
everything I'm doing.

01:08:31.475 --> 01:08:34.109
- As long as you live
in my house, you do.

01:08:35.212 --> 01:08:36.478
- Fine!

01:08:36.479 --> 01:08:39.013
I went to meet Dylan for
a little pre-prom sex

01:08:39.015 --> 01:08:41.416
because I figured he'd
be too drunk after.

01:08:43.185 --> 01:08:45.353
Are you glad you asked?

01:08:48.425 --> 01:08:51.024
- You know, most
mothers are proud

01:08:51.027 --> 01:08:54.028
when their daughters are
about to graduate...

01:08:55.564 --> 01:08:58.032
proud of the women
they've become.

01:08:59.870 --> 01:09:04.872
- Well, then you should
be glowing, Mother.

01:09:07.243 --> 01:09:09.176
- I'm not.

01:09:10.881 --> 01:09:13.113
You don't even deserve
to go to prom.

01:09:16.520 --> 01:09:18.553
- I don't care what you think!

01:09:19.923 --> 01:09:22.023
This is my night!

01:09:24.528 --> 01:09:26.728
I'm gonna be the queen.

01:10:07.637 --> 01:10:10.738
- Oh my gosh! That
limo was so sick!

01:10:10.740 --> 01:10:12.740
- Enjoy prom!
- Oh, you too!

01:10:12.742 --> 01:10:14.375
- Thanks. See you later.

01:10:14.377 --> 01:10:16.544
- OK, guys, let's tag
this moment in history.

01:10:20.951 --> 01:10:22.951
- Hey.

01:10:23.954 --> 01:10:26.988
- Hey. Nice dress!

01:10:26.990 --> 01:10:29.624
Was that the one on
the discount rack?

01:10:30.927 --> 01:10:32.994
- You have to vote
before you go in.

01:10:32.996 --> 01:10:34.462
- I'd love to.

01:10:37.901 --> 01:10:41.269
Is it bad luck to
vote for ourselves?

01:10:41.271 --> 01:10:43.871
- Politicians do
it all the time.

01:10:50.080 --> 01:10:53.081
- Come on, guys.
The party awaits.

01:11:02.592 --> 01:11:04.058
- Hello?

01:11:05.161 --> 01:11:06.961
I'll be right there.

01:11:14.304 --> 01:11:15.570
- Come in.

01:11:16.973 --> 01:11:18.940
- Has Amy gone to prom?

01:11:18.942 --> 01:11:21.276
- Yeah, she left a
short while ago.

01:11:21.278 --> 01:11:22.944
- Um...

01:11:22.946 --> 01:11:26.748
I, uh, I really need you
to take my word on this.

01:11:28.285 --> 01:11:31.886
I would never, ever
strike your daughter.

01:11:31.888 --> 01:11:32.987
- I know.

01:11:36.826 --> 01:11:38.493
- Where did Amy go?

01:11:38.495 --> 01:11:41.663
- Probably to practice
her victory speech.

01:11:42.666 --> 01:11:44.165
- Did you vote for her?

01:11:44.167 --> 01:11:45.400
- Of course!

01:11:46.436 --> 01:11:48.236
Why, didn't you?

01:11:48.238 --> 01:11:49.537
- No.

01:11:50.874 --> 01:11:52.273
- For real?

01:11:52.275 --> 01:11:55.176
Oh my gosh! If Amy finds out,
she is going to kill you!

01:11:55.178 --> 01:11:56.844
- Seriously, Sara?

01:11:56.846 --> 01:11:59.781
She's just a bitch,
not a psycho.

01:12:05.555 --> 01:12:06.988
- Ladies!

01:12:08.525 --> 01:12:09.590
Hey!

01:12:11.127 --> 01:12:14.529
Oh, sweetie, your
makeup looks like crap.

01:12:14.531 --> 01:12:17.265
You should probably go fix it.

01:12:21.705 --> 01:12:23.004
So?

01:12:25.375 --> 01:12:27.041
Did I win?

01:12:28.378 --> 01:12:30.912
- You'll have to wait and see.

01:12:37.721 --> 01:12:40.121
- I knew you were useless.

01:12:40.123 --> 01:12:41.723
- What are you doing?

01:12:41.725 --> 01:12:43.491
- You don't get it, Miya.

01:12:43.493 --> 01:12:46.227
You made a mistake
counting the votes.

01:12:46.229 --> 01:12:47.328
- No, I didn't.

01:12:47.330 --> 01:12:50.298
- You're only here
because of me!

01:12:50.300 --> 01:12:52.767
- Don't touch me, you bitch!

01:12:54.504 --> 01:12:56.304
What the hell?

01:13:00.343 --> 01:13:01.776
- You're pathetic!

01:13:07.150 --> 01:13:09.117
- My mom was right about you!

01:13:09.119 --> 01:13:10.618
- What, you mean that drunk

01:13:10.620 --> 01:13:12.787
that you left to go
live with your dad?

01:13:12.789 --> 01:13:15.423
All because of a cheap bottle
of Chardonnay by the bed?

01:13:15.425 --> 01:13:18.626
You know, it's too bad
it wasn't a better year.

01:13:18.628 --> 01:13:20.762
I might've actually enjoyed it.

01:13:20.764 --> 01:13:24.031
- You're not getting that crown!
Ow!

01:13:25.301 --> 01:13:27.502
- Don't mess with me, Miya.

01:13:27.504 --> 01:13:31.639
I will break you, the same
way that I did your mother.

01:13:37.781 --> 01:13:41.816
- That doll you found
on your door...

01:13:43.653 --> 01:13:46.120
Amy had one just like it.

01:13:46.122 --> 01:13:48.022
I should have spoken up.

01:13:48.024 --> 01:13:53.027
It's just I haven't been able to
mother Amy in such a long time.

01:13:58.334 --> 01:14:01.302
She looks down on me, you know?

01:14:01.304 --> 01:14:03.004
She thinks I'm a failure.

01:14:03.006 --> 01:14:06.174
She should, 'cause you're right.

01:14:06.176 --> 01:14:08.976
I should have raised a child

01:14:08.978 --> 01:14:11.512
who's respectful and kind.

01:14:16.352 --> 01:14:18.686
Amy's none of those things.

01:14:20.190 --> 01:14:21.689
Not anymore.

01:14:23.760 --> 01:14:27.395
You, um, you said you followed
her that night into the woods.

01:14:27.397 --> 01:14:29.230
- Yes, I did.

01:14:29.232 --> 01:14:31.999
- I saw her too.

01:14:32.001 --> 01:14:34.702
She slipped through
the back fence.

01:14:36.172 --> 01:14:39.373
- What do you think
she's doing back there?

01:14:47.383 --> 01:14:49.684
- This used to be
Amy's clubhouse.

01:14:49.686 --> 01:14:52.453
- Why would she still
be coming out here?

01:14:52.455 --> 01:14:54.021
- I don't know.

01:14:56.626 --> 01:14:58.993
I'm sorry. I shouldn't
have brought you here.

01:15:01.364 --> 01:15:02.864
- Do you hear that?

01:15:02.866 --> 01:15:05.032
- It's probably an animal.

01:15:30.093 --> 01:15:31.759
- It's nailed shut!

01:15:47.844 --> 01:15:50.311
- Oh my God!
- Joanne!

01:15:50.313 --> 01:15:51.812
- Oh my God!

01:15:53.082 --> 01:15:55.249
- Elaine, help me get her out!

01:15:58.855 --> 01:16:00.755
Let's get you out of here.

01:16:03.693 --> 01:16:05.159
Are you hurt?

01:16:05.161 --> 01:16:06.727
- No.

01:16:08.431 --> 01:16:09.564
- Oh!

01:16:11.868 --> 01:16:14.468
- What happened? Who
did this to you?

01:16:15.872 --> 01:16:17.338
- Amy Turner.

01:16:17.340 --> 01:16:19.006
- Why?

01:16:19.008 --> 01:16:21.208
- I told her she
wouldn't go to the prom.

01:16:21.210 --> 01:16:24.979
- Oh my God! That's why she
had Miya count the votes!

01:16:24.981 --> 01:16:27.114
If Amy doesn't win...

01:16:29.652 --> 01:16:31.719
Miya, please pick up.

01:16:31.721 --> 01:16:33.287
Call the police.

01:16:33.289 --> 01:16:35.990
- <i>Hi! This is Miya.</i>

01:16:35.992 --> 01:16:37.325
<i>Please leave a message.</i>

01:16:37.327 --> 01:16:39.460
- OK. I'm... I'm
going to the school.

01:16:39.462 --> 01:16:41.729
Tell the police to
meet me there, OK?

01:16:41.731 --> 01:16:44.131
- <i>911, what's your emergency?</i>

01:16:45.635 --> 01:16:47.868
- I need to report my daughter.

01:17:32.215 --> 01:17:35.316
- Hello? Can anyone hear me?

01:17:36.386 --> 01:17:38.619
Please! Can someone hear me?

01:17:38.621 --> 01:17:40.254
Please!

01:17:40.256 --> 01:17:42.456
Please, I'm locked in here!

01:17:46.796 --> 01:17:49.630
- To all my friends,

01:17:49.632 --> 01:17:53.367
peers and fellow students.

01:17:53.369 --> 01:17:58.372
I'm so honoured to
accept this crown

01:17:58.374 --> 01:18:01.409
as your prom queen.

01:18:03.079 --> 01:18:06.614
And I wish you all the
greatest success.

01:18:06.616 --> 01:18:10.951
Because if you really
want it, you can have it!

01:18:30.006 --> 01:18:31.572
- Do you know where Miya is?

01:18:31.574 --> 01:18:33.674
- I don't know. The
auditorium, I think.

01:18:33.676 --> 01:18:35.142
- OK.

01:18:38.448 --> 01:18:40.414
- Ugh!

01:18:40.416 --> 01:18:42.983
To all my friends, peers
and fellow students.

01:18:42.985 --> 01:18:46.287
I'm so honoured to accept this
crown as your prom queen.

01:18:46.289 --> 01:18:48.589
- Do you know where Miya is?

01:18:48.591 --> 01:18:50.758
- I saw her with Amy Turner.

01:18:56.666 --> 01:18:58.666
- Miya?

01:18:58.668 --> 01:19:00.935
Miya!

01:19:00.937 --> 01:19:04.972
- I am so honoured
to accept this crown

01:19:04.974 --> 01:19:06.941
as your prom queen.

01:19:06.943 --> 01:19:10.811
And I wish you all the
greatest success.

01:19:10.813 --> 01:19:13.647
Because if you really want it...

01:19:14.884 --> 01:19:16.851
you can have it!

01:19:25.728 --> 01:19:28.062
- Miya!
- Mom?

01:19:28.064 --> 01:19:29.964
- Miya!

01:19:29.966 --> 01:19:31.665
- Mom! Mom, I'm locked in!

01:19:31.667 --> 01:19:33.567
- Miya!

01:19:33.569 --> 01:19:36.537
- Please! Mom!

01:19:39.876 --> 01:19:41.208
Mom!

01:19:41.210 --> 01:19:42.543
- Are you OK?

01:19:42.545 --> 01:19:44.512
- I'm so sorry. You were right.

01:19:44.514 --> 01:19:46.046
- It's OK.

01:19:46.048 --> 01:19:47.348
- You were right about Amy.

01:19:47.350 --> 01:19:50.351
- It's OK. Let's
get out of here.

01:19:50.353 --> 01:19:54.188
♪♪<i> Call me crazy</i> ♪

01:19:54.190 --> 01:19:55.756
- Let's go dance.

01:19:55.758 --> 01:19:57.825
- What are we gonna do?
- Wait here.

01:19:57.827 --> 01:19:59.493
♪ <i>When I look at my baby</i> ♪

01:19:59.495 --> 01:20:00.761
Amy!

01:20:00.763 --> 01:20:02.863
♪ <i>So crazy</i> ♪♪

01:20:02.865 --> 01:20:05.032
- What are you doing here?

01:20:05.034 --> 01:20:06.500
You were fired, remember?

01:20:06.502 --> 01:20:09.370
You should probably leave
before the principal sees you.

01:20:09.372 --> 01:20:12.773
- I know what you did,
to Miya, to Joanne.

01:20:12.775 --> 01:20:14.608
And for what? For this?

01:20:14.610 --> 01:20:18.579
- Have you been drinking again, Ms.
Taylor?

01:20:18.581 --> 01:20:22.349
Because you're sounding
seriously crazy.

01:20:22.351 --> 01:20:25.519
- I found Joanne.
In your clubhouse.

01:20:25.521 --> 01:20:28.422
- And now, ladies and gentlemen,

01:20:28.424 --> 01:20:31.025
the moment we've all
been waiting for:

01:20:31.027 --> 01:20:34.528
this year's prom king and queen.

01:20:34.530 --> 01:20:36.664
The winners are...

01:20:37.867 --> 01:20:39.867
Amy Turner and Dylan Wade!

01:20:45.441 --> 01:20:47.274
- I won!

01:20:48.778 --> 01:20:51.712
- No. You're gonna pay for
what you did, all of it.

01:20:51.714 --> 01:20:53.981
- Let me go!

01:20:53.983 --> 01:20:55.816
- Come on up and
claim your crown.

01:21:15.605 --> 01:21:18.739
My friends, peers and
fellow students,

01:21:18.741 --> 01:21:22.109
I can't tell you
how honoured I am

01:21:22.111 --> 01:21:25.746
to accept this crown
as your prom queen.

01:21:25.748 --> 01:21:28.816
For years, I have strived

01:21:28.818 --> 01:21:32.453
to represent Avondale
in its excellence

01:21:32.455 --> 01:21:35.489
in everything that I do.

01:21:35.491 --> 01:21:38.525
Because the greatest school
needs the best students.

01:21:38.527 --> 01:21:40.694
And by awarding me this crown,

01:21:40.696 --> 01:21:43.631
you have proven to me
that I am the best!

01:21:46.135 --> 01:21:48.602
What are you doing?

01:21:48.604 --> 01:21:50.871
No! No! No, no, no!

01:21:50.873 --> 01:21:53.340
I haven't finished
my speech yet.

01:21:53.342 --> 01:21:56.110
Get off me! Don't you get it?

01:21:56.112 --> 01:21:58.345
I'm the prom queen!

01:21:58.347 --> 01:22:01.515
This is my moment!

01:22:01.517 --> 01:22:03.717
I deserve this!

01:22:03.719 --> 01:22:06.854
Let me go!

01:22:06.856 --> 01:22:08.956
I deserve this crown!

01:22:09.959 --> 01:22:13.127
Not them! Look at them!

01:22:13.129 --> 01:22:15.629
They're all losers!

01:22:15.631 --> 01:22:17.498
I'm the queen!

01:22:17.500 --> 01:22:19.700
I'm the queen.

01:22:32.982 --> 01:22:36.150
